result.name: Tonkatsu Ginza Bairin

reviews.text: Good tonkatsu at reasonable prices though portions are smaller than at other similar places in HK like Saboten (which is slightly more expensive)

One of the better tonkatsu places in HK. A bit pricey but I think the quality is the same as Tonkichi but cheaper.  Ordered the pork loin kurobuta and I like the way it was cooked. The pork was still succulent unlike others I have tasted from other restaurants. There are other choices like sashimi, tonkatsu curry, and other donburi. The restaurant was also kid friendly with high chair supplements for kids and I saw cute kid plates.
Clean and tasty food...

The fried pork here is very good. It is crispy outside but tender inside.

You can order extra vegetables as much as you like free of charge.
Ok, defo not Tokyo grade

result.name: 銀座梅林

reviews.text:
不過不失，與日本店味道分別不大。
牛肉丼設定為三成熟，筆者只試過二碟有點韌。豬排丼可以。定食可添加椰菜。
冷氣超弱，這裹吃午餐像在火爐中吃食物，大汗淋漓，價格不便宜，但食物一般。
百零蚊一個set,算ok, 吉列豬柳👍🏼唔會好硬，炸得幾好，鬆脆但唔油。另外個set有一大堆椰菜絲，食完減低罪惡感😆。值得一提嘅係，員工會走埋黎問要唔要refill椰菜絲，外面其他同類型舖頭都好少見！
試咗 $188 用日本豬版本的 lunch set，最終發現同平版分別不大，結論係下次可以慳返 😜
食品水準高，價錢中上，清靜乾淨👍
